The paper discusses security issues related to wireless-based solutions, mobile devices, and blockchain technology. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also mentions the Internet of Things (IoT) devices, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of existing infrastructures and devices, which could be related to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also mentions user privacy, which could be related to cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper proposes a novel paradigm for security, which could be related to cs.SE (Software Engineering).
